1 olive oil
1 ciabatta
1 chicken breast strips
1 apple
1 baby spinach leaves
1 Dill & Parsley Mayonnaise
1 slaw mix

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced. Cut or tear ciabatta into chunks.
• Place chicken breast strips on one side of a lined oven tray and ciabatta
chunks on another side.
• Sprinkle Aussie spice blend over chicken. Drizzle everything with olive oil
and season with salt and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then bake until chicken is cooked through
and ciabatta is golden, 10-12 minutes. Set aside to cool slightly.

TIP: If your oven tray is crowded, divide between two trays.

• While chicken and croutons are cooling, thinly slice apple. Roughly chop
baby spinach leaves.

• In a large bowl, combine dill & parsley mayonnaise, a drizzle of olive oil
and a splash of water.
• Add slaw mix, apple, baby spinach and croutons. Season and toss to
combine.

• Divide crouton slaw with creamy herb dressing between plates.
• Top with spiced chicken. Spoon over any resting juices to serve.